observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

reconcile the reciprocal accounts and draw adjusting journal entry to correct the balance of the affected accounts; and

present the appropriate disclosures in the Notes to FS as required under Annex-G of COA Circular No. 2016-004 and COA Circular No. 2015-008 and other relevant disclosures to help readers in better understanding and appreciation of the financial statements;

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

a) strictly evaluate the existence and propriety of all documentary requirements before certifying in the disbursement vouchers as to completeness of supporting documents; and

b) reconstruct the Repair History of all motor vehicles and attach said document on succeeding disbursements for repair. The document should present the reference (JEV/Check No.), date repair was made, amount paid, running balance, the nature of repair and the spare parts procured;

We also recommended the following:
The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to check the sufficiency of the description of the procurement undertaking and require that ABC be indicated in the RFQ to aid the bidder in accurately making its bid;

Management to formulate policy guidelines regarding the release of Assistance to Individuals in Crisis as basis for the grant and release thereof;

Management employ controls such as the issuance of Certification by the Municipal Accountant on the take home pay available for loan repayments before they avail of additional loans from banks and the employee’s Association; and    

Likewise, we recommended that management strictly comply with pertinent laws, rules and procedures in the implementation of projects.

We recommended that Management:

exert best efforts to retrieve reports and related records showing the references and other details of the long outstanding cash advances;


demand settlement of outstanding cash advances to avoid legal sanctions that may be imposed.

We recommended and management agreed to:
Strictly comply with Section 73 (1) of PD No. 1445 on submission of request for relief from accountability;
Strictly comply with the Insurance policies and other procedural guideline pertaining to insurance claims with the GSIS in order to avoid denial of claims and ensure the possibility of recovery of the LGU in cases of accident, loss or damage of its property;
Require the accountable officer to submit documents to prove why they should not be held personally liable for the amount expended on the repairs of the damaged properties; and
Observe the proper allocation and utilization of the local disaster risk reduction and management fund pursuant to JMC of NDRRMC-DBM-DILG No. 2013-1.

We recommended and management agreed that the BAC Secretariat:
furnish the Audit Team with copies of duly perfected contracts together with the pertinent supporting documents within five (5) working days to the Auditor from perfection in accordance with COA Circular No. 2009-001;
post in the PhilGEPS website the Notices of Award and Notices to Proceed for the procurements done thru public bidding and all instances of alternative methods of procurement, except for contracts with ABC of Fifty Thousand Pesos (50,000.00) and below; and
post the procurement opportunity, like Request for Quotation (RFQ) in the PhilGEPS website, the website of the agency concerned, if available, and at any conspicuous place reserved for this purpose in the premise of the Procuring Entity for a period of at least three (3) calendar days;
Likewise, the Municipal Accountant ensures that the printout copy of postings of the Notices of Award and Notices to Proceed in the PhilGEPS website for procurement under public bidding and RFQ, Contract/PO, NOA and NTP, if necessary, for procurement under alternative methods of procurement are included among the supporting documents for payment of procured goods and services.

We recommended that management:

require the Municipal Planning and Development Council and the budget committee during the preparation of annual budget for 20% Development Fund to include only Programs/Projects/Activities which are essential to the promotion of the general welfare of the people;

Implement the development projects programmed during the year as embodied in the Annual Investment/Development Plan and ensure optimum utilization of the 20% Development Fund in compliance with the provisions of DBM-DOF-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular no.  1 dated November 4, 2020;

direct the personnel charged to supervise and monitor the project implementation to make sure that project will be completed in accordance with term and condition of the contract; and

strictly abide with procedure as indicated in the Budget Operations Manual and comply with Section 4(1) of PD No. 1445 to avoid issuance of disallowance.

a. draw adjusting journal entries to correct the balance of affected accounts in the financial statements; 
b. follow the Pro-forma Accounting Entries for income, collection and deposit of RPT as illustrated under Section 69 of GAM for LGUs; and
c. Reconcile the Abstract of Real Property Tax Collections with the Municipal Treasurer based on Real Property Tax Account Register/Taxpayer’s Index Card to update the list of delinquent taxpayers and to determine the actual balance of the Real Property Tax Receivables.

We recommended that Management issue the Notice to Proceed immediately so that it would not delay the project implementation. Also, we recommended that the BAC :
a. ensure that Invitation to Bid, Notices of Award, Notices to Proceed and the approved contracts are posted in the PhilGEPS and website of the agency, in addition to posting of the Invitation to Bid at any conspicuous place reserved for this purpose by the agency; and;
b. strictly comply with the documentary requirements prescribed under COA Circular No. 2012-01 and 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 in all its procurement activities.

We recommended that:
a. Management see to it that all disbursements are duly supported with complete documents in accordance with COA Circular No. 2012-01 and Section4 (6) of PD 1445;
b. Concerned officials fill up all necessary information as called for in the supporting documents particularly in the Pre and Post Inspection Report.

